  "plan": {
    "title": "Plan: Fleet run metadata and Mission Control integration upgrade",
    "overview": "This plan upgrades the existing `extensions/fleet/` implementation so each fleet execution exposes stable, machine-readable run context for Flightdeck/Mission Control while preserving the current operator workflow. The work is scoped as an internal reliability and observability upgrade for pi-clean: fleet should still read `PLAN.md`, split tasks into `.pi/tasks/`, run Claude/Codex/pi engines, render the widget, and archive task folders exactly as before, but the state it writes should become easier for a long-lived dashboard to ingest.\n\nThe key architectural decision is to make all changes additive and backwards-compatible. Existing files such as `.pi/tasks/state.json`, per-task `status.json`, `progress.jsonl`, `output.jsonl`, and `handoff.md` must continue to work, while new files like `.pi/tasks/run.json` and `.pi/tasks/events.jsonl` provide stable run identity, project/git context, heartbeat timestamps, normalized usage, attention hints, and timeline events.\n\nThis is not yet the full Flightdeck application and it does not add mutating web controls for starting or stopping agents. It only prepares fleet's local state model so Flightdeck can consume both historical and active runs more accurately, including degraded support for old task folders that predate these fields.",
    "splitAt": "2026-05-30T09:39:13.583Z",
